statement.tex:
\text{Find the intervals in which the function}\\
f(x) = 3x^4-4x^3-12x^2 + 5\text{ is } \\
\text{(a) strictly increasing (b) strictly decreasing}

step.reason:
\text{In a strictly increasing/decreasing curve }\dfrac{dy}{dx}\neq 0. \\
\text{It can only be }\gt 0\text{ (strictly increasing) or }\lt 0 \\
\text{(strictly decreasing) - but never = 0.}
